messages.content: "Cherry! Get out of here and take Emporio with you!" Jolyne yelled, and Stone Free punched wildly. "It's all gone to hell and I don't want you to die freezing and wet and cold-" Water drips off her hair
She nodded "O-Ok!" She quickly scooped up the boy, stealing a quick glance behind at Jolyne "I love you...." She said to her before starting to run off
"I love you too..." Jolyne tied a string to a dolphin and wrapped the other end around Emporio's and Cherry's wrists with Stone Free. "Pucci won't catch up with the dolphin, go with it."
She nodded again, following the dolphin, watching Jolyne as she did so
Jolyne smiled, and blew a kiss Cherry's way, before cutting the string and falling back, bleeding from so many wounds.
Cherry began crying. God how was she going to get through this...
Jolyne closed her eyes and went limp, and her spirit rose, invisible, to make sure this universe reached it's end conclusion
Cherry was crying still but trying to push on. She had to. For Jolynes sake.

Jolyne watched grimly as time sped up, and Cherry and Emporio were transported to the 'new universe.' Normally just Emporio went but... Pucci strode menacingly around the corner, immediately spotting the two
Cherry held onto Emporio and summoned her stand "Emporio. If I die, run. Run as far away as you can." She said to the little boy
Emporio nodded and stood beside Cherry. Invisibly, Jolyne floated down and put her hands on Cherry's shoulders. "I'm proud of you," she whispered
She couldnt hear her but felt her presence and smiled. "Ill get revenge for you Jolyne." And got ready to fight
"Thank you," Jolyne whispered, and Pucci attacked, sending Whitesnake out with a feint and then a slash to the left
She did her best to defend, using Cherry Bombs hair to try and block
Pucci shook his head slowly. "You could have lived, you know." Whitesnake darted round behind the two and stabbed through, hoping to find its mark
Cherry gasped, holding where she was stabbed "EMPORIO. RUN. GO AND GET AWAY FROM HERE NOW!"
Emporio ran and Pucci kept shaking his head. "Only one more to be eliminated, then.." Emporio darted into his secret room, and Jolyne knelt by Cherry's body. "Hey. Hey Cherry."
She looked at her "Hey Jolyne....I couldn't even get revenge for you huh...."

Jolyne took her hand. "Nuh-uh. You just saved Emporio's life. Sometimes the room he goes into is much closer, and that's when he wins. But now it's further away. You fighting Pucci just gave him time to get to his room and.... Yeah. There's the disc." Jolyne grimaced. "This part's messy. Let's go."
She nodded and held her hand tightly
Jolyne closed her eyes, and they returned to the void, and Shale grimaced. "Well that was an ending.."
She sighed "Yeah....Im...glad I got to meet everyone though...." She smiled at her a small bit
"Yup. I wish they were muns too... I miss them when I die." A single tear rolled down Shale's cheek
She hugged her tightly "I do too....."
"I'll just. Head home." Shale's voice trembled and she wiped away the tears
"Ill...come with you ok...?"
"Yeah." Shale kept trembling and took a shaky step forward
She held her hand
"I'll be fine. This happens a lot."
Jolyne curls up next to a tree. Shes sad, but she doesn't know why

Jotaro walks close bye, not knowing why he was there, but just... being there. Stuffing his hands into his pockets, he walks up to the tree and spots... Jolyne?
“Oi, Jolyne,” he cups a hand to his face and calls to her. For some reason, he gets the feeling that something is wrong.
"...Jota.. Dad?" Jolyne stands up. "What are you doing here?"

He didn’t know. Why *was* he here? Whatever. He just let his gut do the talking.
“I had the feeling my daughter was upset. Want to talk about it?” he holds his arms open for a hug. Huh, usually he doesn’t do that. Weird.
//could Hermes still be here if her mun is... incapacitated?
((Yeah, because shes still her own person
Jolyne nods and hugs him back, even though that's something she wouldn't normally do either. "I just feel. Sad. Like something's missing or I couldn't protect someone.."

Jotaro lightly places a hand on her head, trying to brush his hand through her hair soothingly. “I understand the feeling. Do you want me to do anything, or do you want me to just be here and listen?” he asks.
Hermes walks by with some soda. "Hey, wanna co-" she notices what's happening and runs over
"What's wrong?"
Jolyne wraps her arms around Jotaro more tightly and presses closer to him. "I just want to be quiet for a while... And I just feel sad, Hermes."
Jotaro turns to Hermès and just shakes his head softly, holding Jolyne closer to him.
"...do you need a soda?"
Jotaro glares at Hermès, using Star Platinum to smack her in the back of the head.
Jolyne half laughs, half chokes
"...look, I'm not the best at emotional shit, but..." She just... hugs Jolyne.
Jolyne sighs. "Thank you, Hermes. Thank you, Dad..."
“...” he hummed, just.. existing for a moment.
"I'm always here when you need to talk." She smiled
Jolyne smiles a little, slightly. But its enough to lift her spirits..
*...Something’s wrong,* he realized. He didn’t stiffen, or loosen, or fidget or anything, but he knew something was wrong. He didn’t know what it was, or how he could tell, he just... knew.
Jolyne doesn't notice. She always feels watched, so it doesn't bother her or anything. She just keeps hugging her father
"... Jolyne, can I tell you something?"
"Is it going to upset dad?"
"How does he feel about.... lesbians?"
"I think he's good. Dad?"
Jotaro looked at Hermès with an incredulous face. “I’m gay.”
"Jolyne, I...think I like you." Her face reddened
"Oh. Ohhhhhh." Jolyne blushed. "Hey dad what did you do when you realised you were gay and how do you say you like someone back," she mumbles at him
“...I hid it from everyone because I felt it was unnecessary information. Also, just go,” he let go of Jolyne, leaving only Hermès hugging her.
"Oops. Fair enough. Hermes, I like you back."
"Oh....uhhhhh....dammit the fuck am I supposed to do?! Gloria had the right idea watchin all those fuckin romcoms!"
Her face was super red
"I don't know-" Jolyne hesitates, blushing as well
"Uhhhhhh....you wanna kiss?"
Jotaro crossed his arms, just.. standing there, letting them do their thing.
"Sure." Jolyne leans in and kisses Hermes
*Wow, that was a better way of asking that my way with- with..*
Hernes returns the kiss. Her Kiss (stand) manifests, covering it's face
Jotaro looked at his arms, frow burrowing, confused. *Who did I ask to kiss..?*

Jolyne smiles into the kiss, a very difficult and challenging skill that she manages to do, until her forearm, where her tattoo is, started to hurt a little. The pain went away in a few seconds and she shrugged
Hermes pulled back. "Oh my God....oh my fucking God...."
She seemed unusually giddy
"Hermes? Are you okay?" Jolyne laughs nervously
"Fuck I'm all flustersd-" she says into her hands
Cherry ends up in tge family vacation home. Shes here and trying to act normal.
"Hah!" Jolyne grins, and then frowns. She's been... rubbing her wrist. Why is she rubbing her wrist? Is her tattoo infected?
"You ok?"
“Something’s not right,” Jotaro spoke up now.
"Yeah..."
Mumbling something to himself in Japanese, he looked around. “Something isn’t— ...”
Jolyne tenses up as a stab of pain goes around her tattoo. "What the hell is going on?!"
“Jolyne!” he rushed up to her and grabbed her wrist carefully.
"Yeah?!" Jolyne doesn't pull back like she normally would.
"Jolyne! Do you need me to call a doctor? FF?"

Jotaro.. doesn’t know why he grabbed her wrist. But something isn’t right.
*Something isn’t right.*
“...Cerise,” he mumbles. He doesn’t know why. Who is Cerise?
Jolyne is thinking the same thing. "No, I'm fine, I just.." She tilts her head. "Who's... Ce..rise..?" The name rolls off her tongue, familiar, but she doesn't know how
“...Hermès, do you remember anything..?” Jotaro asks Hermès.
*Wait, “remember anything”? Why did I ask it like that?*
"Should I?!"
Jolyne is confused and she's getting vaguely lightheaded. "Stand attack?"
Cherrys mom suggested that they go on a drive and get some food! Cherry didnt object and they got into the car
“No. Something’s happening— something that...” should? shouldn’t? What the hell is going on...
"That's. Odd." Jolyne looks around suspiciously

I'm a reaper, for god's sake!" She visibly calms herself down. "Maybe I am a hypocrite.... Let's just sort this all out later."

Not like anybody will remember this when they get back anyways.
